<P>Several Rules, Orders, AND By-LAWS Made and Agreed upon By the Free-Holders and Inhabitants of BOSTON OF THE Massachusets, At their Meeting <HI>May,</HI> 12. and <HI>September</HI> 22. 1701.</P>
<P>And Approved by His Majesties Justices for the County of <HI>Suffo<GAP DESC="illegible" REASON="faint" EXTENT="1 letter">k,</HI> at their General Quarter Sessions held at <HI>Boston, August</HI> 5<HI>th.</HI> and <HI>October</HI> 27<HI>th.</HI> next following.</P>
<P>A<GAP DESC="illegible" REASON="faint" EXTENT="3 letters">que Regni Regis <HI>Gulielmi</HI> Tertij <HI>Angliae,</HI> &amp;c. <HI>Decimo Tertio</HI>:</P>
<P><HI>BOSTON:</HI> Printed by <HI>Bartholomew Green,</HI> and <HI>Iohn Allen,</HI> for <HI>Benjamin Eliot,</HI> and are to be Sold at his Shop under the West End of the Town House. 1702.</P>
</DIV1>
